Business Brief -- First Union Corp.:
   Firm Sees Quarterly Net
   At High, Boosts Dividend
The bank holding company said the higher estimate is tied
to strong cost controls and stabilizing credit quality.
   First Union said it expects its provision for loan losses
to be less than in the fourth quarter of 1991, when it
totaled $125 million. The company also said it expects net
charge-offs of bad credits to be lower than the $108 million
it posted in the fourth quarter of 1991. The company said it
believes its nonperforming assets peaked in the third quarter
of 1991.